From aa07d424059c74ea6084a3066d14c26a298a6f70 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 19:50:09 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 7.9 tools webui + SlayzoneToolsHost

Ports the right-side tool-toggle rail onto chrome://slayzone-tools/
following the Phase 7.1 StatusBar recipe. Adds:

- chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/tools.mojom: ToolsHost with
  GetSnapshot() => (ToolsSnapshot) and ToggleTool(id) => (ToolsSnapshot).
  Mirror of the outer packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/tools.mojom.
- slayzone_tools_host.{h,cc}: per-SlayzoneBrowserView Mojo impl.
  GetSnapshot forwards to SidecarClient::Call(tools:get-snapshot);
  ToggleTool forwards id as positional params to tools:toggle;
  response dict -> ToolsSnapshot with ToolToggle list.
- chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_tools_ui.{h,cc}:
  chrome://slayzone-tools/ WebUIController. Serves the
  @slayzone/webui-tools Vite bundle from
  --slayzone-webui-bundle-dir/tools/dist/ (inline error page when the
  flag is missing). CSP + bundle-serving + BindInterface mirror the
  Phase 7.1 statusbar pattern verbatim.
- SlayzoneBrowserView: owns a SlayzoneToolsHost; new tools_host()
  accessor.
- SlayzoneRegionContainer::RegionUrl: routes 'tools' region to the
  dedicated host (replaces the placeholder URL).
- ChromeURLHosts()/webui_url_constants: register
  chrome://slayzone-tools/ host.
- chrome_browser_interface_binders_webui_parts_desktop: registers
  ForWebUI<SlayzoneToolsUI>().Add<ToolsHost>().
- BUILD.gn: new .cc/.h files wired into browser + ui targets;
  mojom/BUILD.gn adds tools.mojom.
